H0.text: Divide change in velocity by change in time is the calculation used to determine acceleration.

H1.text: Multiply average velocity by change in time is the calculation used to determine acceleration.

H2.text: Divide average velocity by mass is the calculation used to determine acceleration.

H3.text: Multiplying change in velocity by distance traveled is the calculation used to determine acceleration.

A4.text: Acceleration is the rate of change of the velocity of an object with respect to time.

A5.text: Average acceleration over a period of time is its change in velocity, Δv, divided by the duration of the period, Δt.
